	</refmeta>
	<refnamediv>
		<refname>&dhproduct;</refname>
		<refpurpose>tool for power management of Sony Vaio laptop devices configuration file</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>
	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<cmdsynopsis>
			<command>&dhproduct;</command>
		</cmdsynopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
		<refsect1 id="syntax">
		<title>SYNTAX</title>
		<para>The configuration file is actually a shell script snippet. Lines starting with hash marks are taken as comments, empty lines are
ignored. Changes to the file should be made only by commenting/uncommenting lines.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="description">
		<title>DESCRIPTION</title>
		<para><citerefentry><refentrytitle>vaiopower</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry> is automatically invoked at boot time,
		and it disables all devices listed in this configuration file.
		</para>
		<para>Support devices are: sound card, DVD drive, Bluetooth and WWAN adapter.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="bugs">
		<title>BUGS</title>
